{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Relevant information about AI model performance should be recorded in a dedicated AI data registry that allows generation of reports across multiple sites and geographies.",
    "Such benchmark data may be useful to individual sites as well as to the AI vendors [79].",
    "At the local level, registry reports would allow institutions to identify performance degradation within their own local environment and could enable a systematic evaluation of the sources of potential data drift on a near real-time basis.",
    "For example, an institution with multiple CT scanners in their clinical workflow might identify performance degradation relative to their own historic performance in an AI model designed to detect intracranial hemorrhage.",
    "Hypothetically, analysis of the aggregate institutional registry data might show the poor performance to be limited to a single machine."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Such benchmark data may be useful to individual sites as well as to the AI vendors [79]."
  ]
}